CrestPoint Capital Management LLC Decreases Position in Bemis Company, Inc. (NYSE:BMS)

					Posted by Michael Walen on Jul 20th, 2017 // No Comments 




CrestPoint Capital Management LLC reduced its stake in shares of  Bemis Company, Inc. (NYSE:BMS) by 13.6% during the second quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the SEC. The firm owned 9,500 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 1,500 shares during the period. CrestPoint Capital Management LLC’s holdings in Bemis were worth $439,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
A number of other large investors also recently added to or reduced their stakes in BMS. Oregon Public Employees Retirement Fund raised its stake in  Bemis by 4.4% in the second quarter. Oregon Public Employees Retirement Fund now owns 35,038 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $1,621,000 after buying an additional 1,475 shares in the last quarter.  Creative Planning raised its stake in  Bemis by 123.6% in the second quarter. Creative Planning now owns 27,926 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $1,292,000 after buying an additional 15,438 shares in the last quarter.  Trust Co. of Vermont raised its stake in  Bemis by 5.9% in the second quarter. Trust Co. of Vermont now owns 14,193 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $656,000 after buying an additional 785 shares in the last quarter.  NEXT Financial Group Inc raised its stake in  Bemis by 31.3% in the second quarter. NEXT Financial Group Inc now owns 2,935 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $136,000 after buying an additional 700 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Bank of Montreal Can raised its stake in  Bemis by 11.2% in the second quarter. Bank of Montreal Can now owns 63,891 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $2,955,000 after buying an additional 6,447 shares in the last quarter. 79.59% of the stock is owned by institutional investors. 


 Get Bemis Company Inc. alerts:



Bemis Company, Inc. (NYSE:BMS) opened at 46.46 on Thursday. Bemis Company, Inc. has a 52 week low of $43.13 and a 52 week high of $53.10. The firm’s 50-day moving average is $45.83 and its 200-day moving average is $47.52. The firm has a market cap of $4.27 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 19.03 and a beta of 0.91. 




Bemis (NYSE:BMS) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, April 27th. The industrial products company reported $0.58 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.65 by $0.07. Bemis had a return on equity of 19.95% and a net margin of 5.73%. The firm had revenue of $995.40 million during the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $996.21 million. During the same quarter in the prior year, the firm earned $0.60 EPS. The firm’s revenue was up 2.8% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, equities analysts anticipate that  Bemis Company, Inc. will post $2.55 earnings per share for the current year. 
