TriMas Corp (TRS) Stake Held by Diversified Trust Co


					Posted by Charlotte Bryant on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments




Diversified Trust Co held its position in shares of  TriMas Corp (NYSE:TRS) during the second quarter, Holdings Channel reports. The institutional investor  owned 9,700 shares of the industrial products company’s stock at the end of the second quarter. Diversified Trust Co’s holdings in TriMas Corp were worth $202,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
A number of other hedge funds and other institutional investors also recently modified their holdings of TRS. Teachers Advisors LLC raised its position in shares of  TriMas Corp by 5.0% in the fourth quarter. Teachers Advisors LLC now owns 76,580 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $1,800,000 after buying an additional 3,628 shares during the last quarter.  First Manhattan Co. raised its position in shares of  TriMas Corp by 4.2% in the first quarter. First Manhattan Co. now owns 2,374,691 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $44,192,000 after buying an additional 96,455 shares during the last quarter.  First Trust Advisors LP raised its position in shares of  TriMas Corp by 37.1% in the first quarter. First Trust Advisors LP now owns 277,720 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $5,763,000 after buying an additional 75,225 shares during the last quarter.  Capital Fund Management S.A. bought a new position in shares of  TriMas Corp during the first quarter valued at $427,000.  Finally, Comerica Bank raised its position in shares of  TriMas Corp by 82.7% in the first quarter. Comerica Bank now owns 186,271 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $4,349,000 after buying an additional 84,311 shares during the last quarter. 


 Get TriMas Corp alerts:



Shares of TriMas Corp (TRS) traded down 0.67% during mid-day trading on Friday, hitting $22.15. 289,025 shares of the company’s stock traded hands. The stock’s market cap is $1.01 billion. The stock has a 50 day moving average price of $21.50 and a 200-day moving average price of $21.75. TriMas Corp has a 1-year low of $17.00 and a 1-year high of $24.25. 





TriMas Corp (NYSE:TRS) last released its earnings results on Thursday, April 27th. The industrial products company reported $0.30 EPS for the quarter, beating the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.28 by $0.02. The firm had revenue of $199.80 million for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $200.40 million. TriMas Corp had a net margin of 3.50% and a return on equity of 5.55%. TriMas Corp’s quarterly revenue was down 1.5% on a year-over-year basis. During the same quarter last year, the company earned $0.27 EPS.  Equities research analysts anticipate that  TriMas Corp will post $1.40 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
